Properties of Verification

Binary (OK or not OK)  --false, may not be binary
defect is defect regardless of severity  --false, severity matters
no defects should be tolerated  --false

Objective
even usability has objective measures  --true

Implicit qualities should be verified --false, don't not verify explicit qualities
Implicit means it's not defined by us, it's inherent.

Explicit qualities should be verified.
because requarementares are often incomplete
eg robustness
